text: Safi N'Diaye (born June 16, 1988) is a French female rugby union player. She represented at the 2014 Women's Rugby World Cup and was named to the Dream Team. She was also a member of the squad that won their fourth Six Nations title in 2014. ==References== Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:French female rugby union players
